              <d1 class="row">
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">General Info</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Soar Base (this app) is built on Ruby on Rails 7 with a PostgreSQL database and Bootstrap 
                    5 CSS styling framework and is deployed on a single dyno in Heroku. Ruby on Rails (Rails) 
                    provides a highly customizable technology stack with far more flexibility than Wordpress 
                    or "off the shelf" solutions.<p>
                    <p>The primary goal of Soar Base is to connect the various user-generated data related to 
                    glider operations into workflows, minimizing redundant data entry and making logging flights 
                    and aircraft reservations as quick and easy as possible. The secondary goal of Soar Base is 
                    to provide all of the settings and analytics needed to run a glider club via a single user 
                    experience, limited by the permission level of the user. </p>

                    <p>Soar Base was developed by Nathan Taylor and is used by the Eagleville Soaring Club under a 
                    perpetual general use license. All rights reserved. </p>

                    <p>Read release notes related to the current version here <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/home/index">Release Notes</a></p>
                    
                    <strong><p>Current version 1.0</p></strong>
                  </dd>
