            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush ">
            <li class="list-group-item lead pb-3" id='reservations'>Reservations
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#top">Back to top</a></li>
              
              <d1 class="row">
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">How to reserve an aircraft, add flights, and pay for flights<br> (Users, Instructors, User Admins)</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Soar base handles flights and reservations differently than our old site. 
                    Reservations are meant to signal that an aircraft will be occupied for a specific time slot on 
                    a specific date. Flights are added to a reservation on or after the reservation date. 
                    Logging flights "inside" of a reservation reduces data entry for users as well as organizing all 
                    flight information and payment status into one place for club leadership. </p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Adding a reservation</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Upon login, each user is redirected to the View My Schedule page. This page shows an availability 
                    grid for the next upcoming flying date (typically Saturdays and Sundays). 
                    Other dates can be selected from the dropdown list and checked by clicking 'Check Reservations' 
                    to repopulate the grid. </p>

                    <p>The availability grid shows open green circles for available times and closed red circles for 
                    unavailable (booked) times. Clicking a green dot opens a form to schedule that selection. User 
                    only needs to select whether they need an instructor and save the reservation.</p>
                    
                    <p>Each reservation shows up below the grid as a card with all relevant info, sorted with 
                    latest date on top. Reservation details can be edited if needed, or the reservation can be 
                    deleted if it is not required or was not flown.</p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Adding a reservation for a private glider</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Private glider reservations do not show up in the grid. Users with private gliders can 
                      add a reservation for a private glider by selecting "Add Reservation" in the navigation 
                      menu and selecting all appropriate information for the reservation. These reservations 
                      will show up in View My Schedule and View Club Schedule and be handled in the same 
                      manner as a normal club reservation.</p>
                  </dd>
                  <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Adding a flight to a reservation</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>On or after the date of the reservation, a button will display to "add flights". This 
                    button will not display for "upcoming" reservations. Clicking this button will open a form 
                    to add a flight to the reservation. Users are asked to provide the tow height, flight 
                    time, confirm the aircraft used, and if needed add the instructor name. Soar Base will 
                    calculate the tow fee using the club's tow pricing schedule. </p>
                    
                    <p>Multiple flights can be 
                    added to a reservation. Once flights have been added to a reservation the reservation 
                    can no longer be deleted. In order to delete the reservation, all flights inside that 
                    reservation must first be deleted. </p>
                  </dd>
                  <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Checkout and payment</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Once flights are added to a reservation, a button will display to "checkout". 
                    This will allow users to checkout and pay via Stripe portal if using credit, debit, 
                    or bank transfer. There is also a selection or payment by check or cash, or logging 
                    that the flight was a Red Tail Hawk flight (to be paid by the paying guest).</p>

                    Payments completed via Stripe show the status as "paid" when completed. Payments 
                    <p>logged as Cash or Check show the status as "pending" until the club treasurer reconciles 
                    the payment method. Flights not paid or pending within 5 days of the reservation date 
                    will be shown as "Past Due". Users are responsible for submitting payment as soon as 
                    possible after flying. </p>
                  </dd>
                  <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Checking the club schedule</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Selecting View Club Schedule from the navigation menu and selecting a specific 
                    date shows all flights reserved for that date by all club members. This view is 
                    useful for instructors and two pilots to see how busy the day is going to be. </p>
                  </dd>
                </d1> 
            </ul>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush ">
            <li class="list-group-item lead pb-3" id='rth_flights'>Red Tail Hawk Flights
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#top">Back to top</a></li>
              
              <d1 class="row">
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">How to reserve a Red Tail Hawk Flight<br> (Commercial Pilots, User Admins)</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Red Tail Hawk flights are handled in much the same way as a normal reservation. The Red Tail Hawk
                    administrator initially logs the reservation under their own name to make sure the aircraft and time
                    slot are reserved, then has the ability to transfer responsibility for the flight to another pilot with 
                    commercial ratings.</p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Adding a reservation - initial reservation</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>The Red Tail Hawk flight administrator uses either the grid view or 'Add New Reservation' nav bar link to
                    select a date, time, and aircraft that the guest is looking for. This ensures that the aircraft and time
                    are reserved.</p>

                    <p>The reservation should indicate that a commercially rated pilot is needed by selecting the
                    "Commercial Pilot needed" flag on the reservation. This step is important as it enables other RTH-specific
                    abilities after the reservation is set up.</p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Transferring a Red Tail Hawk ride to another pilot</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Reservations that are flagged as requiring a commercial pilot can be transferred to another pilot closer
                    to the day of the flight by editing the flight. The Pilot name dropdown will be populated only with Commercially rated
                    pilots to ensure that a non-commercial pilot is not selected. Once this step is completed, the reservation becomes
                    the responsibility of the new pilot.</p>
                  </dd>
                  <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Adding a flight to a reservation</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>On or after the date of the reservation, a button will display to "add flights". This 
                    button will not display for "upcoming" reservations. Clicking this button will open a form 
                    to add a flight to the reservation. This is no different than adding a flight for a personal reservation, incuding the calculation
                    of the tow fees (which the pilot is not responsible for). The only difference is the payment method for a RTH Flight</p>
                
                  </dd>
                  <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Checkout and payment</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Once flights are added to a reservation, a button will display to "checkout". 
                    This will allow a RTH flight to be checked out, just like a regular flight</p>

                    On the Checkout page, the only option available will be 'Checkout RTH Flight'. RTH Pilots
                    should add the guest name to the log before submitting. This will flag the flight as 'pending' so the treasurer
                    can reconcile against the guest payment using the guest name provided.</p>
                  </dd>
                  <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Checking the club schedule</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Red Tail Hawk flights show up with their own Flight type on the Club schedule, so Tow Pilots and other members can easily see what 
                    the day's schedule will be.</p>
                  </dd>
                </d1> 
            </ul>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush ">
            <li class="list-group-item lead pb-3" id='tow_pilots'>Tow Pilots
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#top">Back to top</a></li>
              
              <d1 class="row">
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">How to add duty days and add tow logs for tow pilots</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Soar Base can display the tow pilot scheduled for a given flying day. Since tow planes
                    have different data characteristics than gliders, the "flight log" functionality is 
                    replaced by very similar "tow log" functionality when an aircraft of type 'towplane' 
                    is scheduled by a user. </p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Adding or editing a tow pilot duty day</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Tow pilots can add duty days either by the normal 'Add New Reservation' function, choosing the Pawnee
                    as the aircraft and setting the day and starting hour (usually first available hour). tow pilots can 
                    also navigate to Tow Scheduler -> Tow Pilot Schedule to see the upcoming tow pilot schedule and add themselves to the schedule. </p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Adding or editing a tow log</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>On or after the date specified in the tow pilot schedule, a tow pilot is able to add a tow log to 
                    their reservation. If a tow pilot attempts to add a tow log via the 'View My Schedule' page, then will be redirected to the 
                    normal Tow Scheduler -> Tow Pilot Schedule area via the input form.</p>
                    
                    <p>Tow logs automatically take
                    the tach end from the prior tow log and apply it as the tach start for the new tow log. In cases where the towplane
                    was flown for maintenance this tach start value can be edited. </p>
                  </dd>
                  <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Closing a tow log</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Tow logs must be updated to 'closed' status to signal that the tow log is complete. Tow logs can be closed only
                    after a tow log has been entered via the 'Close Tow Log' button. Modifications are not allowed to closed tow logs, but
                    a closed tow log can be reopened and edited if needed. </p>
                  </dd>
                  <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Monitoring tow plane usage and hours</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Total tows, flight time, and releases can be monitored in the Aircraft List, like all other aircraft. 
                    Since towplanes have different data characteristics, the tables are not the same between gliders and towplanes. 
                    Export funtionality will be added to the towplane logs to allow for offline analysis. </p>
                  </dd>
                </d1> 
            </ul> 
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush ">
            <li class="list-group-item lead pb-3" id='aircraft'>Aircraft
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#top">Back to top</a></li>
              
              <d1 class="row">
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">How to manage aircraft and aircraft users</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Soar Base manages both club aircraft and private aircraft as resources that can 
                    be scheduled. Since club aircraft are shared by all members with the required privileges, 
                    these are shown in the grid view to make reservations simple. Private aircraft are 
                    typically reserved by only one or two people and are not shown in the grid view. </p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Adding or editing an aircraft<br> (Site Admins)</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Aircraft can be added by selecting Aircraft List from the navigation menu and then 
                    selecting Add Aircraft. Populate all required fields and save. This is step 1 of 2 
                    to allow the aircraft to be reserved. Aircraft can also be made "Inactive" by editing 
                    and unselecting the Active Flag. This is important for maintenance or to take an aircraft 
                    offline for a period of time. </p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Adding or editing aircraft users<br> (Site Admins, User Admins)</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Users can only reserve aircraft that they are granted privileges in. For example, a 
                    pre-solo student should not be granted reservation privileges in the ASK-23. Users with 
                    no privileges at all are shown in a separate table at the top. This is step 2 of 2 to 
                    allow an aircraft to be reserved. Adding an aircraft to a user allows them to reserve 
                    that aircraft, private aircraft included. </p>
                  </dd>
                </d1> 
            </ul>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush ">
            <li class="list-group-item lead pb-3" id='memberships'>Memberships
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#top">Back to top</a></li>
              
              <d1 class="row">
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">How to manage user permissions and memberships<br> (User Admins)</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Users are set up at creation with no permissions above the level of users. 
                    Advanced permissions can be added for specific users if they need more capabilities 
                    and functions. Users must also have a valid and current membership in ESC to create 
                    reservations.</p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Adding or editing user permissions </dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>User permissions can be added or edited by selecting Users -> User 
                    Permissions from the navigation menu.</p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Adding or editing User Memberships </dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>User memberships can be added or edited by selecting Users -> User Memberships 
                    from the navigation menu. Users with no membership are listed in a separate table
                     at the top so they can be added. User Memberships must be given a renewal date and 
                     membership type. At the moment membership payments are not handled via Stripe, 
                     but we will likely add this in the future. A user must have an active and not 
                     lapsed membership in order to reserve aircraft or log flights. Grace period on 
                     memberships lapsing is set to zero days after expiration. </p>
                  </dd>
                </d1> 
            </ul>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush ">
            <li class="list-group-item lead pb-3" id='operating-days-hours'>Operating Days and Hours
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#top">Back to top</a></li>
              
              <d1 class="row">
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">How to manage club hours and days of operations<br> (Club Admin)
                </dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Eagleville Soaring Club typically operates on weekend days only, but any other days 
                    can be added as operating days. Hours of operations will fluctuate throughout the season 
                    based on daylight savings time and sunset times. </p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Adding or editing Days of Operation</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Additional flying days can be added to the schedule by selecting Site -> Days of 
                    Operation and adding a new date. In order for a date to show up as a reservation date 
                    it must have the Active Flag selected.</p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Adding or editing Hours of Operation</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Hours of operation can be flagged as active or inactive by editing the Active Flag 
                    for any specific hour. Updating an hour from inactive to active will allow reservations 
                      to be made for that hour and will dynamically render the availability grid with the 
                      new hour. </p>
                  </dd>
                </d1> 
            </ul>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush ">
            <li class="list-group-item lead pb-3" id='faq'>Frequently Asked Questions
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#top">Back to top</a></li>
              
              <d1 class="row">
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Why can I not add flights to a reservation I just made?</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Check the status in the upper right corner of the reservation card, or the reservation 
                    date. If the reservation is in the future no flights can be added yet. 
                    Status will update to "open" on the day of the reservation.</p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Why can't I delete a reservation?</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Check to see if any flights have been added to a reservation. 
                    If a reservation has flights it cannot be deleted. If you need to delete the 
                    reservation, delete the flights first.</p>
                  </dd>
                <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">I want to pre-pay my reservation for next week but don't see a checkout button</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Checkout is not available until the day of the reservation and is also not available 
                    unless flights have been added, which also requires that the reservation date is at least 
                      today. </p>
                  </dd>
                  <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">How do I get a profile picture on the site?</dt>
                  <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                    <p>Profile pics are handled by a universal profile pic service called Gravatar. Click this link to 
                    set up your own profile pic using the same email address that you use for this website.<br>
                    <a class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://gravatar.com/">Create your own Gravatar here!</a></p>
                  </dd>
                  <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Does Soar Base or Eagleville Soaring Club keep my credit card details when I pay?</dt>
                    <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                      <p>No, this site never sees your payment information. All payment information is handled off-site by Stripe, a 
                      PCI level 1 certified payment portal. The only information exchanged between these two sites is your email, 
                      checkout info, and whether the payment was successful or not. Everything else is handled securely between 
                      Stripe and your bank or credit card provider.</p>
                    </dd>
                </d1> 
            </ul>
          
